column2: Table 6#5B# Full-Time Equivalent Employees by Industry
1. Full-time equivalent employees equals the number of employees on full-time schedules plus
the number of employees on part-time schedules converted to a full-time basis.  The number of
full-time equivalent employees in each industry is the product of the total number of
employees and the ratio of average weekly hours per employee for all employees to average
weekly hours per employee on full-time schedules.
